HEADWORD: all-mains
<hw>all-mains</hw> <pos>adj. prenom.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>adaptable to
all voltages; -- of a radio receiver.</def> <mark>[British]</mark>
<note>For power supplies, the term "switching" is used to designate
ability to use more than one voltage as a power source. Typically, it is
used for the ability to use both 110 and 220 volt AC sources.</note>
<illu>an <ex>all-mains</ex> set</illu>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

